==Pronunciation==
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /fis/

==Etymology==
From the French, meaning ''son'', which is from the Latin ''filius''. English usage borrows entirely from French convention to distinguish between a son and father.

===Adjective===
Literally meaning ''son'', word follows directly after a proper name after French grammatical convention. Ex. ''Bush fils, is more informal than father, George H.W. Bush.''

==Noun==
Can be used, though more rarely to refer to the son in context, alone.
"Though Bush pere disparaged it as "Voodoo Economics", '''fils''' has embraced neoliberal, free-market ideology."